<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Morning news posts from Gordon</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=259257" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/027652.html">Server Maintenance</a></B><P>

<I>Hello all,<P>

In preparation for the launch of the EverQuest: The Scars of Velious, roughly 2/3rds of the servers will be taken down, 2-4 per day, over the next week or so. The scheduled downtime page of <a href="http://www.everquest.com">www.everquest.com</a> has been updated to reflect this. <P>

As always we appreciate your continued support and patience as we prepare for the launch of this exciting product.<P>

-Gordon</I><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

Is the release date still on target? Knowing how difficult getting games thru Q/A can be, normally the listed release is normally a bit to bold of a target.<P>

<B>Yes, we're still on target for release. Everyone here is pretty excited and committed to meeting the target. The whole office is buzzing along :)</B><P>

Please, for the love of god, just take them all down at once and get it over with...<P>

<B>That wouldn't be appropriate. The preparations that are being done have some linear components that would require extended downtime in excess of 24 hours were it all to be done at once. <P>

Taking them down 2-4 at a time is the best solution for minimal downtime.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/027655.html">Player morale?</a></B><P>

Does Verant ever take player morale into consideration?<P>

<B>Faxor,<P>

I definitely understand what you are saying and appreciate the way you've stated your thoughts. It's nice to see a good opportunity for straight-forward discussion here on the boards.</B><P>

Doesn't exactly paint a trustworthy picture, does it?<P>

<B>Maybe it does paint a trustworthy picture, but perhaps not in the same fashion as what you would have hoped. I do think that players should and can trust that we'll do what we can in order to ensure that EverQuest remains a game that people want to play. Afterall, it's been shown that people do no like to play games that are too easy and where there is no challenge in playing. It's been shown that there is no feeling of accomplishment that comes, for instance, in obtaining an item that "everyone" else has, or has relatively unrestricted access to. <P>

It's one of those things that can have a positive and negative effect. As has been said before, to make an omelette, you have to break a few eggs.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/027634.html">"Your song has ended abrubtly"</a></B><P>

If this goes live it will show that
you <BR>
a) knew about the bug and did nothing to stop it.<BR>
b) dont give a damn<P>

<B>LyyricalTactics,<P>

Would you mind explaining what you are talking about instead of posting content-free complaints? They do nothing to help... I've read the thread and still don't see what you are talking about. Absor has been sitting here for two hours with a bard trying to reproduce what you are talking about on test. <P>

How about a thorough explanation?<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/027498.html">Will we ever see a Snare or Stun Bow and Arrow set?</a></B><P>

I think a Bow that procs a Snare or Stun spell would be a great addition to EverQuest. <P>

<B>Not arrows. We can't assign an effect to arrows that will proc when the arrows are fired. However, we do now have the ability to create bows that proc an effect. So yes, it is possible that this will be something that you may see in the future.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/027491.html">Any chance of the 'Scheduled Downtime' page being updated ?</a></B><P>

At the moment it does not mention the fact that there was supposed to be a patch today, and not suprisingly it also does not mention that the patch has been cancelled.<P>

<B>So it's basically a wash :) Seriously though, you're correct that there should be something up there, if not concerning the postponed patch then when we're having the next one. I'm talking with ops and test and hope to have another patch scheduled soon. We've got quite a few things going on now with Velious preparations, the launch party in Vegas, and some server maintenance, that things are a bit complicated.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/027453.html">Dx7a won'</a></B><P>

I've tried everything I can think of doing, and still EQ crashes for me between the Server select screen and the
character select screen, after the loading screen. I have run complete file checks and tried 3 drivers from nvidia
and 1 from gateway for my Nvidia Vanta chip. I don't have a soudcard, and this has never caused me problems
before. None of the drivers I have tried (including Detonate 3, the newest driver from nvidia) are certified for
directx 7a. Microsoft lists a compatable version (ver 4.6 bld 3.84) and says to obtain it from the manufacturer,
but neither Gateway nor Nvidia have a driver under this designation. Is my chip compatable? What driver should I
use and where can I get it? Is there something else I'm missing?<P>

<B>Try launching TESTEVERQUEST.EXE. There's some instructions in that patch message considering the order of driver installation and what to do if you have problems. I noticed that you mentioned that you don't have a sound card.... Are you sure? Most computers these days come with them by default. <P>

If you think that your crash may be sound-related, try sticking a file in your EverQuest directory by the name of NOSOUND.TXT. It doesn't matter what's in the file; It's basically a debug tool to let people try with the sound engine disabled.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/027359.html">QA/Bugs/Testing Board: Why is it there?</a></B><P>

Hobart and Ester seem to be AWOL most of the time the past couple months. Posts are starting to get bumped like on General and that isn't good for anyone...<P>

<B>They are busy testing and fixing issues. Communicating on that board isn't part of their official decription, but they asked that the forum be set up to get a better idea of what the players are experiencing.<P>

They aren't there to address issues they've already looked into, but to keep moving forward whenever possible. </B><P>

It is unacceptable to have only one person (Hobart) hired to look into bugs... <P>

<B>Please don't confuse one or two people responding to posts with one or two people looking into issues. Not everyone here is authorized to post on the boards, they are behind the scenes looking into your issues.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/026837.html">Nerfing our Bracer, If only to hide the fact our Epic weapon is so poor</a></B><P>

I heard a rumour that the bracer on test has been given the effect of 'Root'. And that the Winter roar effect will be added to the spear.
Now this in my opinion really blows big if it true. The one peace of kit worth having as shamans could be taken away from us alright at higher levels its more of a toy (lets face it after 55, our spells arent much to get excited about, and you seem intent on giving our best debuffs away to other classes).<P>

<B>Actually we haven't any current plans of "nerfing" the bracer, but to be honest I really don't think that it would be a horrible idea. I wouldn't say that it would be to "hide" anything about the effect on your epic weapon, but it has been said that people didn't like the effect because they'd rather click on the bracer. <P>

Still, like I said, no plans along these lines, but I wouldn't be surprised if it becomes far less available in game.<P>

We are, by the way, changing the effect on the spear to an activatable one in the next patch, if it hasn't been mentioned before.<P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
